<dl id="n12195k"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12195k">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12195k"> 195(k)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ That is essence of a loan</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Prof. Magennis &mdash; Were these payments in the guise of director&apos;s fees, antecedent to the formation of the company? &mdash; No. The four payments made are mentioned in that dossier, and the reasons are given for each payment. For instance, a payment of &pound;10 was made in London because Mr. Figgis said that he had not enough money to get back to Dublin. This is only a loan? &mdash; That may be, but it is still a loan. Such loans always are. <mark>That is the essence of a loan?</mark> &mdash; There were two other payments of &pound;50 each towards Mr. Figgis&apos;s election expenses. <small> <a name="IT29mar24x" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#IT29mar24x"><cite title="source">Irish Times</cite></a> (29 March 1924) 7/4</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
